  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently caught in negative gamma territory with SPX at 6522 sitting between the massive -3.9B gamma wall at 6475 and positive gamma at 6525, meaning they're likely buying this momentum as spot approaches the flip level at 6542. The breakout regime with -1.5B total GEX creates amplifying conditions where any push above 6525 forces dealers to sell into strength, while a rejection back toward 6515-6475 triggers aggressive dealer buying that could fuel further momentum. Watch 6525 as the critical inflection - above this level dealers flip to selling rallies, but below 6515 the stacked negative gamma walls at 6515/6475 create a dealer buying cascade that amplifies any downside move.",
